objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheConnectionProfileCreated SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileIndex u 1 SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileName s EXAMPLE SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileConnectionMode i 0 SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileServerAddressType i 0 SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileServerAddress s EXAMPLE

description: The index of an connection profile instance.
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileIndex

description: A mandadory descriptive name that uniquely identifies a entry in this table. Only this
name will be used as a reference by other configurations to identify this Connection
Profile.
Since configurations may either reference a Connection Profile or Distribution Profile
via its name, the name must be unique across both the sheSecurityConnectionProfileTable
and the sheSecurityDistributionProfileTable.
Note that the following characters may not be used within profile names:
and 'double quotation marks'.
REVISION HISTORY
R4.7.3M: SYNTAX corrected - empty string not allowed.
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileName

description: Connection mode to the server.
VALUES
ftp(0) - Standard FTP without data encryption
sftp(2) - SSH FTP
NOTE
NE does not support FTP over SSH (ftps(1)).
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileConnectionMode

description: Defines the INET address type used to specify the address
of the remote server in
sheSecurityConnectionProfileServerAddress.
VALUES
ipv4(1) : An IPv4 address as defined by the
InetAddressIPv4 textual convention.
ipv6(2) : An IPv6 address as defined by the
InetAddressIPv6 textual convention.
(From SR5.1).
ipv4z(3) : A non-global IPv4 address including a zone
index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z
textual convention.
(From SR5.1).
ipv6z(4) : A non-global IPv6 address including a zone
index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z
textual convention.
(From SR5.1).
dns(16) : A DNS domain name as defined by the
InetAddressDNS textual convention.
(From SR5.1).
NOTES
- Not all applications to which connection profiles may
be assigned may fully support all Inet address types
listed above.
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionProfileServerAddressType

description: Defines the INET address to be used when accessing the
remote server. The type of INET address must be configured
in sheSecurityConnectionProfileServerAddressType.

sheSecurityConnectionFilesListTable and

variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionFileControlListIndex

description: Path name on the remote server, for which a list of files
and directories is required.
This path should be set relative to the server root.
Use only linux notation ( / ).
Spaces in pathnames are not allowed, because of possible
problems with different FTP implementations (client and/or
server).
IMPORTANT NOTE:
Depending on the server configuration, a leading / in the
path configuration could force a write or read action
outside of the user root directory applicable to the
given user account, in which case the path will not be
relative to the root, but will be interpreted as an
absolute path.
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityConnectionFileControlPathName

variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityDistributionProfileName

description: This is a ordered list of valid sheSecurityConnectionProfileIndex values, which are assigned
to this distribution profile. Each listet connectionProfileIndex consist of 2 octets.
The list order is only important in case of file download actions, where only the first profile
in this list will be used for file download.
In case of file upload action, the file will be transfered to all servers which are referenced
by a valid connection profile in this list.
Detailed status information for the file transfer result for each connectionProfile used can be
read from sheSecurityConnectionProfileTable.
variables.name: SHE-SECURITY-MIB::sheSecurityDistributionProfileConnectionProfileList
